summary: Well its happened, I told myself i would cry the day someone tried to compare Villaneve to JokerHarley and i just got into a...
body:
Well its happened, I told myself i would cry the day someone tried to compare Villaneve to JokerHarley and i just got into a debate with a dude on a discord server about it. He said “Well Harley knew what she was getting into” and… no? Its actually specifically mentioned a few times that even though Harley is a bright, educated individual- she was not equipped to deal with the Joker. Infact, there are very few people that can deal with the Joker.

Its like saying that a 15 year old that got into a relationship with a 35 year old has fault because “they knew what they were getting into”. Yes, the 15 yr old DID make that decision but they are not in any way EQUIPPED MENTALLY to make that decision.

title: Wasteland, Baby
description:
by gayforholtzmann

Ever since Villanelle started to work at MI5 with Eve things have been, how do you say, weird? Eve thought it was only noticeable to her. The lingering looks they seemed to share, the way Villanelle appears to just seem interested in what Eve, and Eve alone, is saying. Eve knows what it is, knows what she feels, knows what it means, but she doesn’t dare to label it or give any real acknowledgment to it. That would be dangerous.

Too dangerous.

They dance around each other and play this little game and have for months, Villanelle would push her, Eve would push back, Villanelle would push harder and then Eve would pull away before anything actually happened.

Eve hated it, but deep down she knew that these little interactions with Villanelle, even if it was only ten seconds, made her more excited than ten hours with Niko ever could, ever had. She didn’t know what to do about it.

She knew what she wanted to do.

That’s what scared her.
